Gay Talese, the last titan of the American press
description: He was a pioneer of New Journalism, a movement that transformed American journalism with a literary writing style. At 93, the author of the landmark 1966 profile 'Frank Sinatra Has a Cold,' finds his daily life increasingly constrained by old age.

Tel Aviv's Tarbutat café serves as a fragile haven for Israel's progressive camp
description: The café, which opened two months after the October 7 attacks, is one of the few places in the country where it is still possible to discuss the reality of the war in Gaza. Conceived as a space shielded from political violence, it has nonetheless become a frequent target of far-right activists.

headline: Louvre heist: All suspected members of the commando group now charged
description: A man suspected of being the fourth and final accomplice in the team that stole jewels from the Louvre in broad daylight has been placed in provisional detention. He was already known to authorities.

headline: The housing crisis is fueling the far-right vote
description: In France, a growing share of the population is struggling to find housing. The shortage, which especially affects the working and middle classes, is generating resentment with consequences at the ballot box.
